PARENTS and guardians should stop abusing alcohol in front of children. Drinking problems affect families in a bad way. “Boozing” is only bad if you can’t control your consumption of it. Being an alcoholic is a concern people shouldn’t underestimate. Alcohol destroys families and negatively affects the children from those broken households. Children look up to their parents when they grow up. But if parents drink too much, it becomes a serious crisis. Those who drink alcohol shouldn’t let it to control them.